##################################
#   Annotation how-to.
##################################

for 3D-images e.g. 2D+t or 3D volumetric, itk-snap is a good tool to use for annotation and can be downloaded from <http://www.itksnap.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php>. Windows, Linux and Mac are also usable.

ITK-Snap is built for neuroimaging whose standard imaging formats are not .tif therefore .tif files need to be converted before they can be used.
For python users please install nibabel (https://nipy.org/nibabel/reference/nibabel.nifti1.html)

then run the provided script:
    python export_tif_to_nifti <infile.tif>

where <infile.tif> is the input multi-page tif to convert. 